results.name: Yeezy Boost 350 V2 'Mono Cinder'
results.story: Launching as part of a four-piece ‘Mono’ pack, the adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 ‘Mono Cinder’ applies a black-out finish to the lifestyle sneaker. The revised design features an upper crafted from monofilament mesh, reinforced with an interior cage and accented with a tonal lateral side stripe. A webbing pull tab at the heel allows the sock-like build to be easily slipped on and off. The stealthy palette extends to the midsole, featuring wrapped Boost cushioning that runs the length of the rubber outsole.

results.name: Yeezy 450 'Dark Slate'
results.story: The adidas Yeezy 450 ‘Dark Slate’ delivers a blacked-out iteration of Kanye West’s boundary-pushing silhouette. Stripped of color and exterior branding, the knit upper is secured with an integrated lacing system and topped with an elastic, sock-like cuff. In lieu of a traditional midsole, the rubber outsole sprouts tapered appendages that wrap up the heel and side panels of the deconstructed build, providing support and enhanced durability within its grasp.

results.name: Yeezy Boost 350 V2 'Mono Clay'
results.story: Dropping alongside three companion colorways in a similar one-note finish, the adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 ‘Mono Clay’ updates the minimalist silhouette with an upper constructed from monofilament mesh. The lightweight material is rendered in a pale coral hue and reinforced with an internal cage. A webbing pull tab is affixed to the heel, lining up with tonal stripe detailing on the lateral side. The sneaker rides on a standard full-length Boost midsole with rubber-wrapped sidewalls.

results.name: Yeezy Boost 350 V2 'Mono Mist'
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 ‘Mono Mist’ is taken from the four-piece ‘Mono’ pack, which introduces a refreshed take on the flagship Yeezy sneaker. Traditional Primeknit is replaced by a monofilament mesh upper, finished in a dark beige hue and accented with a tonal lateral side stripe. The sock-like one-piece upper is reinforced with an internal cage and equipped with a webbing heel tab for easy on and off. A full-length Boost midsole, wrapped in semi-translucent rubber for added support and durability, provides responsive cushioning.

results.name: Yeezy 500 'Taupe Light'
results.story: The adidas Yeezy 500 ‘Taupe Light’ steps out in an understated monochromatic colorway that allows the sneaker’s premium construction to come to the fore. Open mesh makes up the majority of the upper, fortified with cow suede and leather overlays throughout. Reflective piping around the eyelets provides a hi-vis element, while a rubber midfoot wrap offers enhanced durability. The layered build is supported by an adiPRENE+ midsole inspired by Kobe Bryant’s third signature shoe, the adidas KB8 3.

results.name: Yeezy Boost 700 'Enflame Amber'
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 700 ‘Enflame Amber’ features muted earth tones on the upper, constructed from breathable beige mesh with dark brown suede overlays throughout the midfoot. A tonal beige toe cap reinforces an unexpected pop of blue mesh on the toe box. Responsive cushioning arrives via a full-length drop-in Boost midsole, housed within a coral-hued EVA carrier and made visible through cut-out detailing on the herringbone-traction rubber outsole.

results.name: Yeezy Boost 700 MNVM 'Bright Cyan'
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN ‘Bright Cyan’ makes use of a lightweight polyester upper, secured with no-tie bungee laces and finished in a vibrant aqua hue. No-sew overlays provide lightweight durability and support, while reflective detailing offers added visibility in low-light conditions. The sneaker’s signature ‘700’ branding adorns the lateral side. Responsive cushioning arrives via sculpted PU midsole, housing full-length Boost cushioning within and reinforced with a herringbone-tread outsole underfoot.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Mono Ice
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 ‘Mono Ice’ represents one of four monochromatic colorways that collectively introduce a refreshed take on the minimalist silhouette. In lieu of traditional Primeknit, the upper is constructed from monofilament mesh, rendered in an icy blue shade and accented with a tonal lateral side stripe. Additional details include an interior cage, webbing heel tab and molded eyelets. A full-length Boost midsole delivers responsive cushioning.

results.name: Yeezy 500 High 'Sumac'
results.story: The adidas Yeezy 500 High ‘Sumac’ treats the bulky silhouette to a unique palette made up of rich earth tones and sharply contrasting primary colors. The upper is constructed from brown mesh with tonal suede overlays at the toe and heel. They’re joined by midfoot suede overlays in blue and indigo, along with bold a crimson overlay that wraps around the collar and snakes underneath the stitched-on eyelets. The sneaker is mounted on a podular adiPRENE+ that offers lightweight cushioning with each step.

results.name: Yeezy 500 High 'Tactical Orange'
results.story: The adidas Yeezy 500 High ‘Tactical Orange’ makes use of a ventilated brown mesh upper with contrasting suede overlays in varying shades of blue. A padded high-cut collar combines with a plush tongue to deliver a snug, comfortable fit, while a brown rubber mudguard offers lightweight support and abrasion-resistant durability. The bulky silhouette rests on a podular adiPRENE+ midsole, modeled after the adidas KB8 3 and finished in a subtle orange hue.

results.name: Nizza Slip-On Low 'Pride Pack - Love Unites'
4DFWD 'Black Solar Red'
results.story: The adidas 4DFWD ‘Black Solar Red’ delivers finely tuned cushioning in a sustainable package. The running shoe’s black Primeknit upper is made in part with recycled materials and zero virgin polyester. A sock-like elastic collar delivers a snug fit, while interior cables are integrated into the lacing system to provide a feeling of midfoot lockdown. The lightweight build rests on adidas’ revolutionary 3D-printed midsole, updated with a bowtie-shaped FWD CELL lattice structure that delivers running economy comparable to the UltraBoost midsole.

results.name: ZX 6000 'Inside Out XZ 0006 Pack - Aqua'
results.story: The adidas ZX 6000 ‘Aqua’ is taken from the ‘Inside Out XZ 0006 Pack,’ featuring a flipped concept initially introduced in the ‘A-ZX series.’ Borrowing a distinctive palette from the OG ZX 8000, the retro runner features a clear TPU overlay atop the aqua-colored textile upper. Zigzag stitching lines the contrasting yellow three-stripes, while forefoot and heel overlays reveal raw exposed-foam edges. A standard EVA midsole is reinforced underfoot by adidas’ Torsion bar and a durable rubber outsole.

results.name: ZX 6000 'Inside Out XZ 0006 Pack - Orbit Grey'
results.story: The adidas ZX 6000 ‘Orbit Grey’ constitutes one-third of the ‘Inside Out XZ 0006 Pack,’ featuring a novel inside-out motif that originally debuted in an installment from the 26-part ‘A-ZX series.’ This pair overlays a clear TPU film atop a light grey textile upper, accented with pink three-stripes and reinforced with exposed-foam overlays at the forefoot and heel. Underfoot, adidas’ signature Torsion bar adds stability to the teal-colored EVA midsole.

results.name: Pharrell x NMD Human Race 'Aqua'
results.story: Taken from a larger collection developed in partnership with the prolific artist, the Pharrell x adidas NMD Human Race ‘Aqua’ showcases monochromatic vibrant blue coloring throughout the sneaker’s exterior. Decorative laces are entwined within structural TPU cages that flank either side of the Primeknit upper, accented with tonal ‘Uluntu’ embroidery across the vamp. The minimalist build rests on a full-length Boost midsole in the same pastel finish.

results.name: ZX 6000 'Inside Out XZ 0006 Pack - Blue'
results.story: The adidas ZX 6000 ‘Blue’ is drawn from the three-piece ‘Inside Out XZ 0006 Pack,’ which revisits the unique inside-out design theme initially unveiled in the ‘A-ZX series.’ A vibrant shade of blue is applied to the textile upper, fortified with a semi-translucent toe wrap and an exposed-foam heel overlay. Coral-hued three-stripes adorn the quarter panel, while a standard adidas Trefoil graces the woven tongue tag. Lightweight cushioning arrives via a beige EVA midsole, accented with an unexpected pop of wraparound pink detailing.

results.name: Aaron Kai x Stan Smith Primeblue Infant 'Doodles'
adidas Yeezy 500 Enflame
results.story: The adidas Yeezy 500 ‘Enflame’ spotlights the sneaker’s adiPRENE+ tooling with a vibrant orange finish. Offering a blend of impact absorption and responsive cushioning, the podular midsole is directly inspired by the adidas KB8 3, released in 1999 as Kobe Bryant’s third signature shoe. Up top, the sneaker’s complex build combines brown open mesh with soft suede overlays in tan, grey and indigo. A rubber midfoot wrap provides added durability and support.

results.name: Five Ten Sleuth DLX Mid 'Grey Gum'
ZX 0000 Evolution 'A-ZX Series'
results.story: Representing the letter ‘E’ in the 26-part collection, the adidas ZX 0000 Evolution ‘A-ZX Series’ reveals an unreleased prototype design meant to bridge the gap between the brand’s iconic ZX and EQT running franchises. The white textile upper is fortified with tonal synthetic suede overlays and accented with bright blue three-stripes trimmed in fuchsia. The same hues are repeated atop the tongue, featuring embroidered branding that reads ‘adidas Torsion ZX ….’ (the four dots indicating ‘to be continued’).

results.name: adidas ZX 0000 Evolution White Bright Blue
Sneakersnstuff x Ultra 4D 'Tee Time'
results.story: The Sneakersnstuff x adidas Ultra 4D ‘Tee Time’ revisits a golf-themed collaboration undertaken by the Three Stripes and the Swedish retailer in 2016. This pair features virtually the same upper used on the original UltraBoost ‘Tee Time,’ highlighted by black and white Primeknit construction with mismatched adidas and SNS branding on each tongue and sockliner. Replacing the older shoe’s Boost cushioning is adidas’ revolutionary 4D midsole, painted black and formed with a blend of light, oxygen and liquid resin.

adidas Flex Disney The Little Mermaid Tail (GS)
adidas Stan Smith Disney The Little Mermaid
results.story: Dropping as part of ‘The Little Mermaid Collection,’ the Disney x adidas Stan Smith ‘King Triton’ takes inspiration from Ariel’s father and the ruler of the undersea kingdom. The deconstructed upper is built with off-white textile that incorporates recycled Parley Ocean Plastic. A tonal trident graphic adorns the heel tab, while the woven tongue tag features adidas and Disney branding in contrasting pops of Bright Cyan. The interior side features a King Triton graphic and an accompanying quote that reads ‘I consider myself a reasonable merman.’ A translucent rubber cupsole anchors the low-top silhouette.

results.name: adidas Superstar Disney The Little Mermaid
results.story: The Disney x adidas Superstar ‘Ariel’ is taken from ‘The Little Mermaid Collection,’ featuring classic silhouettes in a neutral palette that results from sustainable dye technologies. This pair makes use of an ivory-colored leather upper with scaly-textured three-stripes and an embossed seashell graphic on the heel tab. Dual adidas and Disney branding is stamped on the sockliner and tongue tag, the interior side of which is inscribed with a quote from the titular character that reads: ‘I don’t see how a world that makes such wonderful things could be bad.’

results.name: adidas Flex Disney The Little Mermaid Non Dyed (GS)
adidas Gazelle Disney The Little Mermaid
results.story: Drawn from ‘The Little Mermaid Collection,’ the Disney x adidas Gazelle ‘Max’ gives the nod to Prince Eric’s Old English Sheepdog. Standing in for Max’s fluffy coat is shaggy suede detailing on the heel tab and signature three-stripes, while the character’s nose is displayed front and center on the leather tongue tag. The rest of the upper is constructed from off-white leather, produced using sustainable dye technologies that cut down on the use of water, energy and chemicals.

results.name: adidas Ozweego Disney The Little Mermaid
results.story: Launching as part of ‘The Little Mermaid Collection,’ the Disney x adidas Ozweego ‘Ursula’ takes inspiration from the villainous sea witch who conspires to rule the sea kingdom. Neutral off-white and beige tones are applied to a textile upper with tentacle-embossed leather overlays. A leather tongue tag displays dual adidas and Disney branding on the exterior side. The interior side features Ursula’s illustrated likeness, along with a quote that reads ‘Life is full of tough choices, isn’t it?’

results.name: Star Wars x Nizza J 'Intergalactic Race'
adidas NMD R1 Disney The Little Mermaid
results.story: Drawn from the ‘The Little Mermaid Collection,’ the Disney x adidas NMD_R1 ‘Flotsam and Jetsam’ draws inspiration from Ursula’s moray eel henchmen. A monochromatic off-white finish floods the knit upper, produced with sustainable dye technologies that require less water, energy and chemicals. A scaly texture distinguishes the leather heel patch, while the leather tongue tag features adidas and Disney branding. The interior tongue is decorated with a graphic depicting the villainous duo, along with a quote that assures the wearer, ‘Don’t be scared.’
